    "details": {
      "blurb": "The Gray Mistress; the queen's regretful general",
      "languages": {
        "details": "",
        "value": [
          "common"
        ]
      },
      "level": {
        "value": 14
      },
      "privateNotes": "",
      "publicNotes": "<p><strong>Role (EVENT 2):</strong> the queen's general and lover — long disillusioned (Trinia, the conditioning, the plague, the devils), secretly softening the Maidens' cruelty. Her gambit: fly <strong>Zarmangarof</strong> (the charmed black dragon — link @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.pathfinder-bestiary.Actor.Lvdykf6wfqzZBlZd]{Black Dragon (Ancient)}, run at CR-15 weight) over the city to bait the PCs, sabotage the beast from the saddle, and <strong>fight it beside them when it turns on her</strong>. After: she casts down her sword, bares her face, confesses everything, and asks for redemption — castle intelligence, and the city Maidens rallied to the rebellion. <strong>She never attacks the PCs.</strong> (+2 RP for the dragon, +1 for defeating her — +3 for sparing and recruiting her.)</p>",
      "publication": {
        "title": "Pathfinder: Curse of the Crimson Throne (PF2e conversion, private)",
